[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     32[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe OpenSearch index used here is created on first run if it doesn't exist.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m In production, the index is created by infrastructure-as-code (CDK/Terraform/CloudFormation) with proper field mappings, refresh intervals, and a documented schema versioning policy. Don't let application code own index creation in production.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     33[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAll providers, patients, and engagement events in the example are synthetic.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Do not treat any specific NPI, provider name, or patient_id as real. A production system ingests from a real credentialing feed and joins to real patient profiles under BAA.[K
